EMI Group Ltd., the music company
that  Citigroup Inc. (C) , its owner, plans to sell this summer,
increased annual profit last year by 7 percent to 330 million
pounds ($535 million), the Sunday Times reported.  Len Blavatnik, the billionaire businessman whose Access
Industries Holdings LLC agreed on May 6 to buy Warner Music
Group, is the favorite among candidates to purchase London-based
EMI for an estimated 3.5 billion pounds, the newspaper said,
without citing anyone.  To contact the reporter on this story:
